abstract: >
  Holor Calculus IX presents the Conjugate Awareness Holon as a synthesis of
  Holor Calculus I–VIII: awareness formalized as a 0D manifold equipped with a
  Spiral Time metric tau, a non-Abelian morpheme ontology, and an admissibility
  operator P_adm acting as a conservation law for ethically admissible flow.
  The classical singularity is reframed as a conjugate throat, and key
  boundary behavior at the curvature cap is formalized via an elastic
  reflection corollary. The record remains technically legible and interiorly
  faithful, containing formal statements, proof sketches, and explicitly
  labeled open hypotheses.
